label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas without regional lymph node metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension; or in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension; or in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with metastasis in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN2c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage II Burkitt Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (II); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in association with regional lymph node involvement with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (IIE).

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pN3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with metastasis in a lymph node, more than 6 cm in greatest dimension.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system. TNM clinical findings are based on inspection and palpation of the involved area and the regional lymph nodes.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas without distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system. TNM pathologic findings are based on the histologic examination of the regional lymph nodes following focused (sentinel lymph node biopsy), therapeutic, or complete lymphadenectomy.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.  The TNM pathologic and clinical primary tumor classifications of Merkel cell carcinoma are the same. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Antithyroid Agent

value.value: A pharmacological agent that acts as a thyroid hormone antagonist. Antithyroid agents may inhibit thyroid hormone production.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage III Burkitt Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm (III), which also may be accompanied by extralymphatic extension in association with adjacent lymph node involvement (IIIE) or by involvement of the spleen (IIIS) or both (IIIE,S).

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma with no evidence of primary tumor (e.g., nodal/metastatic presentation without associated primary). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Nerve Conduction Velocity Test

value.value: A test that measures the speed of nerve activity along the length of a nerve. It is used to detect nerve damage or dysfunction.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with a finding of in situ primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with less than or equal to 2 cm maximum tumor dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Tympanometry

value.value: The study of the mobility of the tympanic membrane and conduction bones through air pressure changes. It is used to detect middle ear abnormalities.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with greater than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm maximum tumor dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Flat Tympanometry Result

value.value: A tympanometry test result indicating the lack of movement of the tympanic membrane due to middle ear pathology.

label.value: Retracted Tympanometry Result

value.value: A tympanometry test result indicating the retraction of the tympanic membrane resulting from negative ear pressure.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with over 5 cm maximum tumor dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma characterized by a diffuse proliferation of predominantly large neoplastic B lymphocytes.  It is the most frequently seen type of non-Hodgkin lymphoma, representing 30%-40% of the cases.  Morphologic variants include centroblastic lymphoma, immunoblastic lymphoma, and anaplastic lymphoma.  Subtypes/entities include T-cell/histiocyte rich large B-cell lymphoma, primary diffuse large B-cell lymphoma of the central nervous system, plasmablastic lymphoma, primary cutaneous diffuse large B-cell lymphoma, leg type, and ALK-positive large B-cell lymphoma.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with primary tumor invading bone, muscle, fascia, or cartilage. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Hypoproteinemia

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating abnormally low levels of total protein in the serum.

label.value: Socialization

value.value: The process of learning and adopting behavioral patterns that conform with the surrounding culture.

label.value: NHEJ1 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in DNA repair and V(D)J recombination.

label.value: NHEJ1 wt Allele

value.value: Human NHEJ1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2q35 and is approximately 85 kb in length. This allele, which encodes nonhomologous end-joining factor 1 protein, plays a role in the mediation of both V(D)J recombination and the repair of damaged DNA. Mutation of the gene is involved in a form of severe combined immunodeficiency.

label.value: Nonhomologous End-Joining Factor 1

value.value: Non-homologous end-joining factor 1 (299 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human NHEJ1 gene. This protein is involved in both the repair of double-strand breaks in DNA and nonhomologous end-joining.

label.value: Catecholamine

value.value: A group of sympathetic amines containing a catechol group derived from the amino acid tyrosine. Catecholamines are hormones and neuromodulators synthesized in the chromaffin cells of the adrenal glands and the postganglionic fibers of the sympathetic nervous system in response to stress. Examples of catecholamines are epinephrine (adrenaline), norepinephrine (noradrenaline) and dopamine, all of which participate in a wide variety of functions throughout the body.

label.value: ORAI1 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in calcium transport and T-cell-mediated immune responses.

label.value: ORAI1 wt Allele

value.value: Human ORAI1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12q24.31 and is approximately 15 kb in length. This allele, which encodes calcium release-activated calcium channel protein 1, is involved in the modulation of both T-cell pathogen response and calcium influx. Mutation of the gene is associated with congenital severe combined immunodeficiency.

label.value: Calcium Release-Activated Calcium Channel Protein 1

value.value: Calcium release-activated calcium channel protein 1 (301 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human ORAI1 gene. This protein plays a role in both the regulation of cellular calcium concentration and the transcription of pathogen responsive genes.

label.value: Recurrent Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: The reemergence of diffuse large B-cell lymphoma after a period of remission.

label.value: NPPB Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in cardiac homeostasis.

label.value: NPPB wt Allele

value.value: Human NPPB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p36.2 and is approximately 1 kb in length. This allele, which encodes natriuretic peptides B, plays a role in diuresis, vasorelaxation and regulation of renin and aldosterone secretion.

label.value: Natriuretic Peptides B

value.value: Natriuretic peptides B (134 aa, ~15 kDa) is encoded by the human NPPB gene. This protein is involved in the maintenance of cardiac homeostasis.

label.value: Brain Natriuretic Peptide 32

value.value: Brain natriuretic peptide 32 (32 aa, ~3 kDa) is encoded by the human NPPB gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of diuresis, vasorelaxation and secretion of renin and aldosterone.

label.value: N-Terminal Fragment Brain Natriuretic Protein

value.value: N-terminal fragment brain natriuretic protein (76 aa, ~9 kDa) is encoded by the human NPPB gene. This protein is a marker for cardiac failure.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  The TNM pathologic and clinical regional lymph nodes classifications of Merkel cell carcinoma are not the same. TNM pathologic regional lymph nodes findings are based on the histologic examination of the regional lymph nodes, following focused (sentinel lymph node biopsy), therapeutic, or complete lymphadenectomy.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with negative regional lymph nodes by pathologic examination. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis in regional lymph node(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
